Rinsola Abiola, a daughter of the late business mogul, Moshood Kasimawo Abiola, has obtained expression of interest and nomination forms to contest the position of a national youth leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC). She obtained her forms at the national secretariat of the APC in Abuja, ahead of the March 26 convention of the party. 75% of Nigeria’s budget lost to corruption – Forensic experts PDP to Buhari: Address challenges facing Nigerians She thanked her supporters for identifying with her aspiration since she made it public. Miss Abiola assured that if elected, she would protect the interests of young progressives and mobilise youth votes for the APC during the 2023 general elections. She served in the Eighth Assembly as an aide to the then Speaker of the House of Representatives.